{"artifact_links": ["https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/23/seth-larson"], "author_or_org": null, "canonical_url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/23/seth-larson", "collection_method": "rss_atom", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "e8769a18f81e8aa6", "dedup_key": "rss-guid:simonwillison-blog:https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/23/seth-larson/#atom-everything", "event_id": "event_a94bd0056cb7aa24", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "<blockquote cite=\"https://blog.pypi.org/posts/2026-07-22-releases-now-reject-new-files-after-14-days/\"><p>The Python Package Index (PyPI) now rejects new files being uploaded to releases that are older than 14 days. This restriction was\u00a0<a href=\"https://github.com/pypi/warehouse/pull/19727\">put in place</a>\u00a0to prevent old and long-stable releases from being poisoned in case publishing tokens or workflows of PyPI projects were compromised. As far as we are aware this has not yet been abused, but there is no technical reason beyond that attackers weren't aware it was possible.</p></blockquote>\n<p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://blog.pypi.org/posts/2026-07-22-releases-now-reject-new-files-after-14-days/\">Seth Larson</a>, PyPI blog</p>\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/packaging\">packaging</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/python\">python</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/supply-chain\">supply-chain</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/pypi\">pypi</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/seth-michael-larson\">seth-michael-larson</a></p>", "identifiers": {}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "rss_atom_item", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-07-23T04:50:36+00:00", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-07-23T22:23:10Z", "source_id": "simonwillison-blog", "source_name": "Simon Willison's Weblog", "source_native_id": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/23/seth-larson/#atom-everything", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "primary_artifact", "summary_hint": "<blockquote cite=\"https://blog.pypi.org/posts/2026-07-22-releases-now-reject-new-files-after-14-days/\"><p>The Python Package Index (PyPI) now rejects new files being uploaded to releases that are older than 14 days. This restriction was\u00a0<a href=\"https://github.com/pypi/warehouse/pull/19727\">put in place</a>\u00a0to prevent old and long-stable releases from being poisoned in case publishing tokens or workflows of PyPI projects were compromised. As far as we are aware this has not yet been abused, but there is no technical reason beyond that attackers weren't aware it was possible.</p></blockquote>\n<p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://blog.pypi.org/posts/2026-07-22-releases-now-reject-new-files-after-14-days/\">Seth Larson</a>, PyPI blog</p>\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/packaging\">packaging</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/python\">python</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/supply-chain\">supply-chain</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/pypi\">pypi</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/seth-michael-larson\">seth-michael-larson</a></p>", "title": "Quoting Seth Larson", "topics": ["topic_quoting-seth-larson"], "updated_at": null}
{"artifact_links": ["https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/22/thomas-ptacek"], "author_or_org": null, "canonical_url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/22/thomas-ptacek", "collection_method": "rss_atom", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "f05ea79f276dda6d", "dedup_key": "rss-guid:simonwillison-blog:https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/22/thomas-ptacek/#atom-everything", "event_id": "event_f67bb6a00a2f0978", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "<blockquote cite=\"https://twitter.com/tqbf/status/2080045032162173329\"><p>I genuinely believe that if you took an open weights model from 2025 and built a pentest harness for it, it could do this kind of sandbox escape and scan/hack in most networks. This is only surprising because you assume OpenAI has sounder sandboxes.</p></blockquote>\n<p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tqbf/status/2080045032162173329\">Thomas Ptacek</a>, doesn't think <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/22/openai-cyberattack/#resist-the-temptation-to-write-this-off-as-a-stunt\">this even needs</a> a frontier model</p>\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/thomas-ptacek\">thomas-ptacek</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/openai\">openai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/security\">security</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-security-research\">ai-security-research</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai\">ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llms\">llms</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/sandboxing\">sandboxing</a></p>", "identifiers": {}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "rss_atom_item", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-07-22T23:59:01+00:00", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-07-23T22:23:10Z", "source_id": "simonwillison-blog", "source_name": "Simon Willison's Weblog", "source_native_id": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/22/thomas-ptacek/#atom-everything", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "primary_artifact", "summary_hint": "<blockquote cite=\"https://twitter.com/tqbf/status/2080045032162173329\"><p>I genuinely believe that if you took an open weights model from 2025 and built a pentest harness for it, it could do this kind of sandbox escape and scan/hack in most networks. This is only surprising because you assume OpenAI has sounder sandboxes.</p></blockquote>\n<p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tqbf/status/2080045032162173329\">Thomas Ptacek</a>, doesn't think <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/22/openai-cyberattack/#resist-the-temptation-to-write-this-off-as-a-stunt\">this even needs</a> a frontier model</p>\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/thomas-ptacek\">thomas-ptacek</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/openai\">openai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/security\">security</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-security-research\">ai-security-research</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai\">ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llms\">llms</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/sandboxing\">sandboxing</a></p>", "title": "Quoting Thomas Ptacek", "topics": ["topic_quoting-thomas-ptacek"], "updated_at": null}
